Title:
inlineExecute (Cobalt Strike BOF for in-process .NET execution with ETW/AMSI patching)

Type:
GitHub Tool

Short Summary (4–8 sentences max):
- This repository provides a Cobalt Strike Beacon Object File (BOF) that loads and executes a .NET assembly inside the current Beacon process instead of using `execute-assembly` with a sacrificial process.  
- It focuses on reducing telemetry by implementing ETW bypasses in `clr.dll` via Provider Handle Patching and Subscriber Bit Patching, based on the author’s “A Stealthier Reflective Loading” write-up.  
- The ETW approach aims to avoid common suspicious primitives (e.g., `VirtualProtect`, `WriteProcessMemory`) by not changing memory protections.  
- It also includes an AMSI bypass targeting `clr.dll` by modifying `g_amsiContext` and `AmsiScanBuffer`-related globals located in read/write memory, again avoiding memory-protection flips.  
- A `-scan` mode identifies patchable values/addresses using x64 instruction signatures to help validate offsets per `clr.dll` build.  
- Useful for red team operators/pentesters experimenting with stealthier in-process .NET tradecraft and researchers evaluating detection opportunities around CLR/ETW/AMSI manipulation.

Technical Focus:
- Cobalt Strike BOF in-process .NET assembly execution
- CLR hosting (`clr.dll`, `ICorRuntimeHost`) and AppDomain execution
- ETW bypass: Provider Handle Patching
- ETW bypass: Subscriber Bit Patching
- AMSI bypass via `g_amsiContext` / `AmsiScanBuffer` global manipulation
- Signature-based offset discovery for patching across `clr.dll` versions

Use Cases:
- Execute tools like Rubeus/SharpHound-style .NET assemblies without spawning a child process
- Reduce/alter ETW telemetry emitted by CLR during managed code execution
- Bypass AMSI scanning for managed execution paths in-process
- Research and prototype alternative patching methods that avoid `VirtualProtect`/WPM patterns
- Validate detection engineering ideas by observing CLR global/ETW structure tampering

Keywords:
Cobalt Strike, BOF, Beacon, inline execution, .NET assembly, CLR hosting, clr.dll, ICorRuntimeHost, AppDomain, ETW, Event Tracing for Windows, Provider Handle Patching, Subscriber Bit Patching, AMSI, AmsiScanBuffer, g_amsiContext, userland telemetry, signature scanning, x64 assembly, in-process execution